When <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> business people take up an expatriate lifestyle , the thing they worry about most is family matters , especially the education of their growing children .
For <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> expatriates in mainland <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">China</ENAMEX> , incompatibility between the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> and mainland education systems is the main reason why most of them do not move their families across with them .
In the city of <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Dongguan</ENAMEX> , located just over <ENAMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">40 kilometers</ENAMEX> east of <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Guangzhou</ENAMEX> , the ground has already been broken on a project to build the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</ENAMEX> school for <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> children in mainland <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">China</ENAMEX> .
