There are a number of reasons why family members are unwilling to move to the mainland -
some spouses have jobs in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Taiwan</ENAMEX> , crime is a concern on the mainland , and the quality of medical care is not so good there .
For people with families , however , the key stumbling block is the quality of education .
Asks <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sylvia Yang</ENAMEX> , deputy chairperson of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">TBAD</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Women 's Division</ENAMEX> , " What are we working to achieve , anyway ?
