Where to send the kids ?
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">H. D. Ye</ENAMEX> notes that there are now about <ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">400</ENAMEX> children of <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> expatriates in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Dongguan</ENAMEX> who attend school in the mainland .
<ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">Greater than half</ENAMEX> attend mainland <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">China</ENAMEX> 's regular elementary and secondary schools , while the more affluent <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> send their children to private schools for expatriate children .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Chang Mei - liang</ENAMEX> , chairperson of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">TBAD</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Women 's Division</ENAMEX> , is among the latter group .
After her elder son and daughter finished elementary school in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Taiwan</ENAMEX> she sent them to a boarding school in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Britain</ENAMEX> .
